<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-11-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Ehrman</persName> to
                                    Mr. <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Panama</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-11-07"><hi rend="italic">November 7,
                                        1903</hi>.</date><lb/>(Received 12.20
                                p.m.)</dateline></opener>
                            <p>I have communicated to Panama Government that they will be held
                                responsible for the protection of the persons and property of
                                citizens of the United States, as well as to keep the isthmian
                                transit free in accordance with obligations of existing treaties
                                relative to the isthmian territory.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Ehrman.</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>